<H1>Standards</H1>
<H2><A id=3D02 name=3D02></A>FIPS PUB 140-2 - Effective 15-Nov-2001</H2>
<H3>Security Requirements for Cryptographic Modules</H3>
<P>NVLAP accredited Cryptographic and Security Testing (CST) =
Laboratories=20
perform conformance testing of cryptographic modules. Cryptographic =
modules are=20
tested against requirements found in <STRONG>FIPS PUB 140-2, =
<EM>Security=20
Requirements for Cryptographic Modules</EM></STRONG> [ <A class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/fips/fips140-2/fips1402.pdf"=20
target=3D_blank>PDF</A> ]. Security requirements cover 11 areas related =
to the=20
design and implementation of a cryptographic module. For each area, a=20
cryptographic module receives a security level rating (1-4, from lowest =
to=20
highest) depending on what requirements are met. </P>
<P>An overall rating is issued for the cryptographic module, which =
indicates (1)=20
the minimum of the independent ratings received in the areas with =
levels, and=20
(2) fulfillment of all the requirements in the other areas. On a =
vendor's=20
validation certificate, individual ratings are listed, as well as the =
overall=20
rating. <STRONG>It is important for vendors and users of cryptographic =
modules=20
to realize that the overall rating of a cryptographic module is not =
necessarily=20
the most important rating. The rating of an individual area may be more=20
important than the overall rating, depending on the environment in which =
the=20
cryptographic module will be implemented (this includes understanding =
what risks=20
the cryptographic module is intended to address).</STRONG></P>
<H3>FIPS PUB 140-2 Annexes:</H3>
<P>Annex A: Approved Security Functions [ <A class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/fips/fips140-2/fips1402annexa.p=
df"=20
target=3D_blank>PDF</A> 05-30-2012]<BR>Annex B: Approved Protection =
Profiles [ <A=20
class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/fips/fips140-2/fips1402annexb.p=
df"=20
target=3D_blank>PDF</A> 08-12-2011]<BR>Annex C: Approved Random Number =
Generators=20
[ <A class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/fips/fips140-2/fips1402annexc.p=
df"=20
target=3D_blank>PDF</A> 02-16-2012]<BR>Annex D: Approved Key =
Establishment=20
Techniques [ <A class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/fips/fips140-2/fips1402annexd.p=
df"=20
target=3D_blank>PDF</A> 01-02-2013]</P>
<H3>Testing Requirements:</H3>
<P>Cryptographic module validation testing is performed using the =
<EM>Derived=20
Test Requirements</EM> [DTR] <EM>for FIPS PUB 140-2, Security =
Requirements for=20
Cryptographic Modules</EM> [ <A class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/documents/fips140-2/FIPS1402=
DTR.pdf"=20
target=3D_blank>PDF</A> 01/04/2011]. The DTR lists all of the vendor and =
tester=20
requirements for validating a cryptographic module, and it is the basis =
of=20
testing done by the CST accredited laboratories.</P>
<H3>Implementation Guidance:</H3>
<P>NIST and CSEC have developed an <EM>Implementation Guidance for FIPS =
PUB=20
140-2 and the Cryptographic Module Validation Program</EM> [ <A =
class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/documents/fips140-2/FIPS1402=
IG.pdf"=20
target=3D_blank>PDF</A> 12-21-2012] document for cryptographic module =
users,=20
vendors and testing laboratories. This is intended to provide =
clarifications of=20
CMVP programmatic guidance, FIPS 140-2, FIPS 140-2 Derived Test =
Requirements,=20
testing guidance, and guidance related to the implementation of Approved =
or=20
non-Approved security functions.</P>
<H3>Validation List:</H3>
<P>NIST maintains the <A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/validation.html">FIPS 140-1 =
and FIPS=20
140-2 Cryptographic Modules Validation List</A> of all validated FIPS =
140-1 and=20
FIPS 140-2 cryptographic modules. An alphabetical list of FIPS 140-1 and =
FIPS=20
140-2 vendors (vendors with validated cryptographic modules) is also =
available=20
along with the underlying data base which the validation listing are =
generated=20
from. The posted validation listing represents the official valdiation=20
information. </P>
<H3>Other Information:</H3>
<UL class=3Dbullets1>
  <LI>FIPS PUB 140-2 was signed on May 25, 2001 and became effective =
November=20
  15, 2001 when the Derived Test Requirements for FIPS PUB 140-2, =
<EM>Security=20
  Requirements for Cryptographic Modules</EM> was published. </LI>
  <LI>The CMVP accepted test reports from CST laboratories against =
either FIPS=20
  140-1 or FIPS 140-2 and the applicable DTR from November 15, 2001 to =
May 25,=20
  2002 when the transition period ended. </LI>
  <LI>After May 25, 2002, the CMVP will only accept test reports against =
FIPS=20
  140-2. </LI>
  <LI>All previous validations against FIPS 140-1 WILL STILL BE=20
  RECOGNIZED.</LI><BR>
  <UL>
    <LI>FIPS PUB 140-2 Page v, <STRONG>Implementation Schedule:</STRONG> =

    "<EM>Agencies may retain and use FIPS 140-1 validated products that =
have=20
    been purchased before the end of the transition period.</EM>"=20
    <STRONG>Clarification:</STRONG> Agencies may continue to purchase, =
retain=20
    and use FIPS 140-1 validated products after May 25, =
2002.<BR></LI></UL>
  <LI><A class=3Dpdf=20
  =
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/nistpubs/800-29/sp800-29.pdf"=20
  target=3D_blank><STRONG>Special Publication 800-29: A Comparison of =
the Security=20
  Requirements in Cryptographic Modules in FIPS 140-1 and FIPS=20
  140-2</STRONG></A></LI><BR>
  <LI><A class=3Dpdf=20
  =
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/documents/fips140-2/140-2flo=
w.pdf"=20
  target=3D_blank>Diagram</A> that maps the general flow of the CMVP =
FIPS 140-2=20
  testing process.</LI></UL><BR><BR><A class=3DtopLink=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/standards.html#top">Back to =
Top</A>=20
<H2><A id=3D03 name=3D03></A>FIPS PUB 140-1 - Transition Ended =
25-May-2002</H2>
<H3>Security Requirements for Cryptographic Modules</H3>
<P>NVLAP accredited Cryptographic Module Testing (CMT) laboratories =
perform=20
validation testing of cryptographic modules. Cryptographic modules are =
tested=20
against requirements found in <STRONG>FIPS PUB 140-1, <EM>Security =
Requirements=20
for Cryptographic Modules</EM></STRONG>, [ <A class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/fips/fips140-1/fips1401.pdf"=20
target=3D_blank>PDF</A> ]. Security requirements cover 11 areas related =
to the=20
design and implementation of a cryptographic module Within most areas, a =

cryptographic module receives a security level rating (1-4, from lowest =
to=20
highest), depending on what requirements are met. For other areas that =
do not=20
provide for different levels of security, a cryptographic module =
receives a=20
rating that reflects fulfillment of all of the requirements for that =
area.</P>
<P>An overall rating is issued for the cryptographic module, which =
indicates (1)=20
the minimum of the independent ratings received in the areas with =
levels, and=20
(2) fulfillment of all the requirements in the other areas. On a =
vendor's=20
validation certificate, individual ratings are listed, as well as the =
overall=20
rating. <STRONG>It is important for vendors and users of cryptographic =
modules=20
to realize that the overall rating of a cryptographic module is not =
necessarily=20
the most important rating. The rating of an individual area may be more=20
important than the overall rating, depending on the environment in which =
the=20
cryptographic module will be implemented (this includes understanding =
what risks=20
the cryptographic module is intended to address).</STRONG></P>
<H3>Testing Requirements:</H3>
<P>Cryptographic module validation testing is performed using the =
<EM>Derived=20
Test Requirements for FIPS PUB 140-1</EM> [ <A class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/documents/fips140-1/1401test=
.pdf"=20
target=3D_blank>PDF</A> ] and <EM>Derived Test Requirements for FIPS PUB =
140-1=20
APPENDIX A, A Cryptographic Module Security Policy</EM> [ <A class=3Dpdf =

href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/documents/fips140-1/1401test=
A.pdf"=20
target=3D_blank>PDF</A> ]. It lists all of the vendor and tester =
requirements for=20
validating a cryptographic module, and it is the basis of testing done =
by the=20
CMT accredited laboratories.</P>
<H3>Implementation Guidance:</H3>
<P>NIST and CSEC have developed an <EM>Implementation Guidance for FIPS =
PUB=20
140-1 and the Cryptographic Module Validation Program</EM> [ <A =
class=3Dpdf=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/documents/fips140-1/FIPS1401=
IG.pdf"=20
target=3D_blank>PDF</A> 01-10-2002] document for cryptographic module =
users,=20
vendors and testing laboratories. This is intended to provide =
clarifications of=20
CMVP programmatic guidance, FIPS 140-1, FIPS 140-1 Derived Test =
Requirements,=20
testing guidance, and guidance related to the implementation of Approved =
or=20
non-Approved security functions.</P>
<H3>Validation List:</H3>
<P>NIST maintains the <A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/validation.html">FIPS 140-1 =
and FIPS=20
140-2 Cryptographic Modules Validation List</A> of all validated FIPS =
140-1 and=20
FIPS 140-2 implementations. An alphabetical list of FIPS 140-1 and FIPS =
140-2=20
vendors (vendors with validated cryptographic modules) is also available =
along=20
with the underlying data base which the validation listing are generated =
from.=20
The posted validation listing represents the official valdiation=20
information.</P>
