<H2><A id=3D04 name=3D04></A>International Standards</H2>
<H3>ISO/IEC 19790 Information technology - Security techniques - =
Security=20
requirements for cryptographic modules</H3>
<P>ISO/IEC 19790 1st Edition was published 2006-03-01</P>
<P>ISO/IEC 19790 2nd Edition was published 2012-08-15</P>
<P>It was prepared by Joint Technical Committee ISO/IEC JTC 1, =
Information=20
technology, Subcommittee SC 27, IT Security techniques. ISO/IEC 19790 =
1st=20
Edition was derived from NIST Federal Information Processing Standard =
(FIPS) PUB=20
140-2, <I>Security Requirements for Cryptographic Modules</I>.</P>
<P>The CMVP does not validate cryptographic modules tested for =
conformance to=20
ISO/IEC 19790<STRONG>.</STRONG></P>
<P>Copies of ISO/IEC 19790 may be obtained at <A=20
href=3D"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/www.iso.org"=20
target=3D_blank>http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/STM/cmvp/www.iso.org</A></P>
<H3>ISO/IEC 24759 Information technology - Security techniques - Test=20
requirements for cryptographic modules</H3>
<P>ISO/IEC 24759 1st Edition was published 2008-07-01. </P>
<P>It was prepared by Joint Technical Committee ISO/IEC JTC 1, =
Information=20
technology, Subcommittee SC 27, IT Security techniques. This =
International=20
Standard was derived from NIST Derived Test Requirements for FIPS PUB =
140-2,=20
<I>Security Requirements for Cryptographic Modules</I>.</P>
<P>ISO/IEC 24759 is currently undergoing revision to be aligned with =
ISO/IEC=20
19790 2nd Edition. The 1st Committee Draft (CD) was circulated for NB =
comment=20
3Q2012.</P>
